r\neq 1
n
a
r
a + ar + a r^2 + a r^3 + \cdots + a r^{n-1} = a\cdot \frac{1-r^{n}}{1-r}.
\text{Let }s = a + ar + ar^2 + ar^3 + \cdots + ar^{n-1}.
\text{Then }rs = ar + ar^2 + ar^3 + ar^4 + \cdots + ar^{n}
\text{Then }s - rs = a-ar^{n}
\text{Then }s(1-r) = a(1-r^{n}),
\text{ so }s = a \frac{1-r^{n}}{1-r}.
